Access Control Models
controlling access means reulating who is authorized to tak a particular action, whether viewing/modifying files or accessing certain physical locations

the following are popular methods of implementing access control policies:
Mandatory access control
discretionary access control
attribute bassed access control
role based access control
rule bassed access control

Mandatory Access control:
A means of restricting access to system resources based on the sensitivity of the information contained in the system resource and the clearance of users to access
the information 

Discretionary Access Control:
A means of restricting access to objects where the owner of the object has full control and is able to change the permissions of other users as they pertain to the
object and its data - the controls are discretionary in the sense that accessibility is changed at the owners discretion

